5.  Container Overview  (Level 2) 

The system is composed of five internal containers. Each container is an independently deployable unit with a distinct responsibility. Tech-stack decisions are deferred. 

 

Container 

Responsibility 

Frontend SPA 

The single-page web application that patients, schedulers, and administrators use to interact with the system. It handles all UI rendering, navigation, and user flows. 

Auth Service 

Manages the entire authentication lifecycle: magic-link generation, MFA, OAuth token acquisition, session creation, idle-session expiry, and rate-limiting of login attempts. 

Appointment Service 

Orchestrates all appointment actions — booking, rescheduling, and cancellation. It enforces business rules (conflict checks, no-show windows, reschedule windows), coordinates with external systems, and publishes audit events for every state change. 

Notification Service 

Schedules and dispatches appointment reminders (push, email, SMS) and records delivery status and patient responses. It reacts to appointment events so it can send confirmations and cancellation notices. 

Audit Log Service 

Accepts immutable log events from all other services and persists them in an append-only store. Provides a read-only query interface for compliance and reporting purposes. 

 

