Query real-time slot availability; commit or release bookings. 

Appointment Service 

→ EHR System 

Sync appointment status changes. 

Appointment Service 

→ Billing System 

Push appointment data for invoicing. 

Appointment Service 

→ Notification Service 

Trigger confirmation and cancellation notifications. 

Notification Service 

→ Email/SMS Gateway 

Dispatch reminder messages. 

All Services 

→ Audit Log Service 

Emit immutable audit events for every state change. 

System Administrator 

→ Monitoring Service 

Monitor health, uptime, and alerts. 

 

8.  Security & Compliance Principles 

The following security and compliance principles apply across the entire system. Implementation details (specific libraries, configurations) are out of scope at this stage. 

 

Concern 

Requirement 

Data in Transit 

All communication between the browser, internal services, and external systems uses TLS 1.3. 

Data at Rest 

All stored data (appointments, user records, audit logs) is encrypted with AES-256. 

Authentication 

Passwordless: magic link or biometric prompt. Short-lived OAuth 2.0 tokens. MFA codes expire within 5 minutes. Idle sessions expire after 30 minutes. 

Authorization 

Role-based access control (RBAC) ensures patients can only access their own records; schedulers and administrators have scoped permissions. 

Audit Trail 

Every action is logged in an immutable, tamper-evident audit store. Entries are retained for a minimum of 24 months (or longer for regulatory compliance). 

 

9.  Deferred Decisions 

The following topics are explicitly out of scope for this document and will be addressed in subsequent design artefacts: 

 

Technology stack (languages, frameworks, cloud provider, databases, message brokers) 

Data models and schema design 

API contracts and route definitions 

Deployment topology and infrastructure configuration 

